      "writtenOn": "2019-05-23T22:55:42Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "I think this could legitimately happen, since BT is only eventually consistent. Maybe try re-reading the OPS a couple more times before giving up?\n\nAlternatively, store a revision number in each OPS that\u0027s incremented at each update. Store the revision of the OPS in each trace. When loading, find the max OPS revision across traces and keep re-reading the OPS until you get a new-enough version. (If you do this, you don\u0027t really need to store the hash of the OPS.)",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 283,
        "startChar": 0,
        "endLine": 287,
        "endChar": 4
      },
      "revId": "7879f6a199678d985ba85c77b2a244a55066b336",
      "serverId": "5086850b-e599-37d2-8ec8-ff16aeccbf02",
      "unresolved": true
